---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div style="text-align: center; border-bottom: 1px solid #ffffff;">
				<h1>What is MUN Concrete Toboggan?</h1>
			</div>
			<div style="text-align: center">
				<p>
					Concrete Toboggan is a diverse student group from the Memorial University of Newfoundland and 
					Labrador (MUN). The team includes five engineering sub-teams which are mechanical, concrete, 
					logistics, marketing, spirit/display. A team of students from various backgrounds and 
					disciplines that come together and build a concrete toboggan for the annual GNCTR.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div style="text-align: center; border-bottom: 1px solid #ffffff;">					
				<h1>Sub-Teams</h1>
			</div>
		<div class="dropdown-container">
			<div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-around; text-align: center">
				<details>
					<summary><img src="path_to_icon1.png" alt="Icon 1"> <br> Mechanical Design Team</summary>
					<p>The mechanical team works on designing the superstructure and straing and breaking sysems for the toboggan.</p>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary><img src="path_to_icon2.png" alt="Icon 2"> <br> Concrete Design Team</summary>
					<p>The concrete team works on designing the skis for the toboggan.</p>
				</details>
			</div>
			<div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-around; text-align: center">
				<details>
					<summary><img src="path_to_icon3.png" alt="Icon 3"> <br> Logistics Team</summary>
					<p>The logistics team works on budgeting and fundrasing for the competition.</p>
				</details>
				<details>
					<summary><img src="path_to_icon4.png" alt="Icon 4"> <br> Marketing Team</summary>
					<p>The marketing team works on budgeting and fundrasing for the competition.</p>
				</details>
			</div>
			<div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-around; text-align: center">
				<details>
					<summary><img src="path_to_icon5.png" alt="Icon 5"> <br> Spirit/Display Team</summary>
					<p>The spirt/display team works on theme for the toboggan and the display for the competition day.</p>
				</details>
			</div>
		</div>
			<div style="text-align: center; border-bottom: 1px solid #ffffff;">
				<h1>About the Competition</h1>
			</div>
			<div style="text-align: center">
				<p>
					The Great Northern Concrete Toboggan Race (GNCTR) is the largest student run, engineering 
					competition in Canada. The annual competition includes a technical exhibit, presentations 
					and multiple racing events spanning over a five day period. On race day, team's are judged 
					on various aspects of their toboggan such as their speed, steering & braking design in a 
					slalom race and can compete in the ultimate King of the Hill tournament.
				</p>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
details {
	margin: 1em 0.5em;
	text-align: center;
	/* border-bottom: 1px solid #ffffff; */
}
summary {
	font-weight: bold;
	cursor: pointer;
}

details summary {
    font-size: 30px; /* Adjust as needed */
    padding: 10px; /* Adjust as needed */
    cursor: pointer; /* Change the cursor to a pointer */
}

details p {
    font-size: 25px; /* Adjust as needed */
    padding: 10px; /* Add some padding */
}

.dropdown-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: space-around;
    text-align: center;
	max-width: 80vw; /* Limit the width of the container to 80% of the viewport's width */
    margin: 0 auto; /* Center the container */
}

.dropdown-container div {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-around;
    text-align: center;
    width: 100%; /* Make the divs take up the full width of the container */
}

.dropdown-container details {
    flex: 1 0 40%; /* This means the dropdowns will take up 40% of the container's width, and they will wrap to the next line if there isn't enough space */
    margin: 1em 0.5em;
}

.dropdown-container summary {
    font-weight: bold;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.dropdown-container details p {
    max-width: 60%; /* Limit the width of the text to 90% of the container's width */
    margin: 0 auto; /* Center the text */
}
</style>